<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="51" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="51">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="51">
The species name 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="51">siamense</emphasis>
was derived from the exonym 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Siam”">&quot;Siam&quot;</normalizedToken>
, a term formerly used as the name of Thailand. The name was chosen in recognition of Thailand as the center of the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="species’">species'</normalizedToken>
known distribution (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1670/16-064" author="Siler, CD" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Herpetology" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" pagination="332 - 347" refId="B18" refString="Siler, CD, Heitz, BB, Davis, DR, Freitas, ES, Aowphol, A, Termprayoon, K, Grismer, LL, 2018. New Supple Skink, Genus Lygosoma (Reptilia: Squamata: Scincidae), from Indochina and Redescription of Lygosoma quadrupes. Journal of Herpetology 52 (3): 332 - 347, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1670/16-064" title="New Supple Skink, Genus Lygosoma (Reptilia: Squamata: Scincidae), from Indochina and Redescription of Lygosoma quadrupes." url="https://doi.org/10.1670/16-064" volume="52" year="2018">Siler et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="51">
The grammatical gender of the generic nomen 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Lygosoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygosoma" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="51">Lygosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hardwicke &amp; Gray, 1827 has been confused in the literature where it was treated as both feminine (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1670/16-064" author="Siler, CD" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Herpetology" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" pagination="332 - 347" refId="B18" refString="Siler, CD, Heitz, BB, Davis, DR, Freitas, ES, Aowphol, A, Termprayoon, K, Grismer, LL, 2018. New Supple Skink, Genus Lygosoma (Reptilia: Squamata: Scincidae), from Indochina and Redescription of Lygosoma quadrupes. Journal of Herpetology 52 (3): 332 - 347, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1670/16-064" title="New Supple Skink, Genus Lygosoma (Reptilia: Squamata: Scincidae), from Indochina and Redescription of Lygosoma quadrupes." url="https://doi.org/10.1670/16-064" volume="52" year="2018">Siler et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
) or neutral (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1093/zoolinnean/zlz001" author="Freitas, ES" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" pagination="1067 - 1096" refId="B8" refString="Freitas, ES, Datta-Roy, A, Karanth, P, Grismer, LL, Siler, CD, 2019. Multilocus phylogeny and a new classification for African, Asian and Indian supple and writhing skinks (Scincidae: Lygosominae). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 186 (4): 1067 - 1096, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1093/zoolinnean/zlz001" title="Multilocus phylogeny and a new classification for African, Asian and Indian supple and writhing skinks (Scincidae: Lygosominae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1093/zoolinnean/zlz001" volume="186" year="2019">Freitas et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
). The nomen 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Lygosoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygosoma" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="51">Lygosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is probably based on the Greek nouns &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="51">lygos</emphasis>
&quot;and &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="51">
<normalizedToken originalValue="sōma">sōma</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
&quot;, meaning 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“supple-bodied”">&quot;supple-bodied&quot;</normalizedToken>
, and the gender of this nomen is neutral. Consequently, the ending of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Siler, Heitz, Davis, Freitas, Aowphol, Termprayoon &amp; Grismer" authorityYear="2018" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Lygosoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygosoma siamensis" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="siamensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="51">Lygosoma siamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
provided by its original description should be modified as &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="51">siamense</emphasis>
&quot;.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
